## PHASE 3: THE RANKING ENGINE

After all five differentiation questions are answered for each surviving candidate, produce a composite score:

```
COMPOSITE SCORING:
  Moat Stack:              X/15 (weight: 30%)
  Agentic Score:           X/4  (weight: 20%)
  NRR Trajectory:         X/5  (weight: 25%)
  Management Quality:     X/9  (weight: 15%)
  10x Math:               ✅/⚠️/❌ (weight: 10% — binary)

COMPOSITE CALCULATION:
  Moat: (X/15) × 30 = [X] points
  Agentic: (X/4) × 20 = [X] points
  NRR: (X/5) × 25 = [X] points
  Management: (X/9) × 15 = [X] points
  Math: 10 if ✅, 5 if ⚠️, 0 if ❌

TOTAL: X/100
```

**Ranking tiers:**
- 80–100: PRIMARY CANDIDATE — highest conviction, build full thesis
- 65–79: SECONDARY CANDIDATE — monitor, build thesis on price weakness
- 50–64: WATCHLIST — revisit in 12 months or on significant new data
- Below 50: ELIMINATE — does not meet 10x threshold in this theme

