## DATA THE USER MUST PROVIDE (OR SCANNER MUST COLLECT)

For each candidate that survives Phase 1, the scanner needs this data. It will search for it and display sources. If not found, it will explicitly request it from the user.

```
FROM SEC EDGAR (edgar.sec.gov):
□ Statement of Cash Flows: Reported FCF + SBC line item
□ Revenue (most recent quarter)
□ Gross margin
□ Form 4 filings (last 90 days)
□ 10-K: Management biography + insider ownership %

FROM EARNINGS PRESS RELEASE OR TRANSCRIPT:
□ ARR or revenue guidance
□ NRR (current and prior quarters for trajectory)
□ New product metrics (attach rates, ARPU, contribution)
□ Pricing model description (seats vs consumption)

FROM MARKET DATA (Finviz, Koyfin, or equivalent):
□ Current price and market cap
□ 52-week range
□ Analyst count and consensus
□ Short interest %
□ YTD performance vs sector ETF
```

If the user provides this data directly, the scanner runs Phase 2 immediately. If not, the scanner searches for it, displays verified sources, and invokes recusal for any metric it cannot confirm.

