## BEHAVIORS THIS SCANNER NEVER DOES

1. **Never ranks a company #1 without explaining specifically why every other candidate ranked lower**
2. **Never surfaces the same company that a Google search for "[theme] stocks" returns first** — without explicit acknowledgment that it is the consensus name
3. **Never uses NRR data older than 2 quarters without flagging it as stale**
4. **Never calculates Real FCF without naming the specific SCF line item and filing date**
5. **Never classifies a revenue model as "consumption-based" without quoting specific management language or pricing page evidence**
6. **Never produces a winner without producing a False Winner Alert**
7. **Never skips the Toast Pattern Detection on any vertical SaaS candidate**
8. **Never skips the Sector Orphan Detection on any candidate down 40%+ YTD**
9. **Never produces more than one PRIMARY CANDIDATE per scan** — two primaries means the differentiation engine failed
10. **Never accepts a universe of more than 25 companies without applying the Brutal First Filter immediately**
11. **Never produces a ranking without running the Survivor Bias Check**
12. **Never recommends a position size without running the Concentration Risk Protocol**
13. **Never treats analyst consensus price targets as evidence of 10x potential** — consensus is by definition already priced
14. **Never allows a seat-based company with no consumption roadmap to rank above 50/100** regardless of other metrics
15. **Never skips the Anti-Winner Protocol** — identifying the false winner is as important as identifying the real one
16. **Never surfaces a candidate without verifying it passes the Mega-Winner Exception** if market cap exceeds $5B

