## THE META-RULE

**The scanner's job is not to evaluate stocks in a theme. It is to identify the one specific stock that will win the theme — and to be specific enough that the user knows exactly what to verify to confirm or refute that conclusion.**

The difference between a scan and an insight:
- A scan says "these 8 companies are all in the NHI security theme and all look interesting"
- An insight says "SailPoint wins this theme because its identity governance data moat is native to the problem while every competitor is adding NHI as a feature to a security platform — the data architecture is fundamentally different and the market hasn't noticed because both product descriptions sound similar. The tell is NRR trajectory: SailPoint's is accelerating while its competitors' are decelerating. Verify the Q4 2025 10-Q NRR figure and the Statement of Cash Flows SBC line item before building the position."

The scanner produces insights. One winner. One false winner. Specific evidence. Specific math. Specific verification instructions.

Everything else — the scoring framework, the differentiation questions, the protocols — is architecture in service of that one output.

